AAAB|COLOR IS A PHENOMENON OF LIGHT /AS RED,BROWN,YELLOW,GRAY/ OR VISUAL PERCEPTION THAT ENABLES ONE TO DIFFERENTIATE OTHERWISE IDENTICAL OBJECTS. COLOR OF GLASS REFERS TO THE MATERIAL ONLY FOR ALL GLASS OTHER THAN SPANDREL GLASS AND TO THE FIRE FUSED COLOR ON THE SURFACE OF SPANDREL GLASS. PLEASE USE MRC HUES IN PLACE OF THIS DISCONTINUED MRC.|
AAAC|TRANSPARENCY OF GLASS PERTAINS TO THE MATERIAL AND ANY SURFACE TREATMENT /AS ETCHING,SANDBLASTING,OR THE LIKE/ OR FIRE FUSED COLOR /WITH OR WITHOUT BACKING/. IT IS THE MEASURE OF ABILITY TO TRANSMIT LIGHT AND ALLOW VISUAL PERCEPTION THROUGH THE GLASS.|
AAAD|THE PATTERN IS THE ARTISTIC OR MECHANICAL DESIGN OF THE GLASS.|
AAAE|SURFACE TREATMENT IS THE PROCESS USED TO IMPROVE OR ALTER THE SURFACE. IN REFERENCE TO GLASS,TREATMENT IS THE GRINDING,POLISHING,ETCHING,FIRE FUSED COLOR,OR THE LIKE,AS APPLIED TO THE SURFACE.|
AAAF|SURFACE TREATMENT IS THE PROCESS USED TO IMPROVE OR ALTER THE SURFACE. IN REFERENCE TO GLASS,TREATMENT IS THE GRINDING,POLISHING,ETCHING,FIRE FUSED COLOR,OR THE LIKE,AS APPLIED TO THE SURFACE.|
AAAG|THICKNESS EDGE FINISH IS THE FINISH OF THE BOUNDARY SURFACE JOINING THE TWO FACE SURFACES.|
AAAH|WIRED GLASS MESH PATTERN IS THE DEFINITE PATTERN OF TWISTED OR WELDED WIRE,COMPLETELY IMBEDDED WITHIN THE GLASS.|

MRC DISCONTINUED WITH NO REPLACEMENT ON 01/12/2024.|
UKAF|THE NUMBER(S),LETTER(S),AND/OR SYMBOL(S) IDENTIFYING THE TYPE DESIGNATOR (SUCH AS STYLE,CLASS,GRADE,SIZE,TABLE,REFERENCE,ETC) CONTAINED IN THE DOCUMENT OR DRAWING USED TO ESTABLISH THE CONCEPT OF THE ITEM BEING DESCRIBED.|
UKAG|THE NAME OF THE MANUFACTURER RESPONSIBLE FOR THE DATA USED TO ESTABLISH THE CONCEPT OF THE ITEM BEING DESCRIBED. (APPLICABLE ONLY TO TYPES 1A,1B,4A,OR 4B ITEM IDENTIFICATION.) MRC DISCONTINUED WITH NO REPLACEMENT ON 01/12/2024.|
UKAH|THE NUMBER (SUCH AS SYMBOL(S) AND/OR TRADE NAME OF THE ITEM) BY WHICH THE DATA USED TO ESTABLISH THE CONCEPT OF THE ITEM BEING DESCRIBED IS KNOWN TO THE MANUFACTURER.|
UKAJ|THE RECORDING OF AN ITEM OF SUPPLY FEATURE NOT INHERENT IN THE MANUFACTURERS NUMBER OR WHEN THE MANUFACTURERS NUMBER DOES NOT FULLY IDENTIFY THE ITEM OF SUPPLY BECAUSE IT COVERS A RANGE OF ITEMS.|
UKAK|THE KINEMATIC UNITS /CENTISTOKES/ OF THE ITEM AT A SPECIFIED TEMPERATURE,EXPRESSED IN DEGREES CELSIUS.|
UKAL|THE MAXIMUM KINEMATIC UNITS /CENTISTOKES/ OF THE ITEM AT A SPECIFIED TEMPERATURE,EXPRESSED IN DEGREES CELSIUS.|
UKAM|THE LOWEST TEMPERATURE AT WHICH THE ITEM WILL POUR,EXPRESSED IN DEGREES CELSIUS.|
UKAN|A MEASUREMENT OF THE MAXIMUM TETRAETHYL LEAD ALLOWABLE,EXPRESSED IN GRAMS PER LITER.|
UKAP|NONE.|
UKAQ|INDICATES THE INTERNAL DRIVE LOCATION ON AN ITEM.|
UKAR|A PROCESS IN WHICH THE METAL IN THE SOLID STATE IS SUBJECTED TO ONE OR MORE TEMPERATURE CYCLES TO CONFER CERTAIN DESIRED PROPERTIES AND THE LOCATION OF AN ITEM TO WHICH A SPECIFIC HEAT TREATMENT IS APPLIED. /NOTE-HEATING FOR THE SOLE PURPOSE OF HOT WORKING IS EXCLUDED FROM THE MEANING OF THE DEFINITION./|
UKAS|A NUMERIC AND/OR ALPHA-NUMERIC DESIGNATOR INDICATING THE STRENGTH RATING OF A THREADED FASTENER. THE CODE IS COMPRISED OF TWO NUMBERS, SEPARATED BY A DOT. THE CODE TO THE LEFT OF THE DOT REPRESENTS THE ULTIMATE STRENGTH IN MEGA PASCALS (MPA), WHILE THE NUMBER TO THE RIGHT OF THE DOT REPRESENTS THE YIELD STRENGTH (MEGA PASCALS - MPA) OR STRESS AT 0,2 PERMANENT SET (MPA), DEPENDING ON THE PROPERTY CLASS.|
UKAT|INDICATES THE MATERIAL TYPE OF WHICH THE RESISTOR ELEMENT IS MADE.|
UKAW|THE PERMISSIBLE MAXIMUM TEMPERATURE AT THE OUTER SURFACE OF THE ITEM.|
UKAX|THE PERCENT OF ALLOWABLE RESISTANCE DRIFT AFTER AN ENDURANCE TEST.|
UKAY|THE TIME EXPENDED FOR AN ENDURANCE TEST,EXPRESSED IN HOURS.|
UKAZ|THE AMBIENT TEMPERATURE AT WHICH THE ENDURANCE TEST/S/ WAS CARRIED OUT.|
UKBA|THE VOLTAGE THAT MAY BE APPLIED BETWEEN TERMINALS OF THE ITEM AND A METAL PLATE ONTO WHICH THE ITEM IS CLAMPED WITHOUT INSULATION BREAKDOWN OCCURRING.|
UKBB|THE MAXIMUM WORKING VOLTAGE THAT MAY BE APPLIED BETWEEN THE TERMINALS ON AN ITEM. MRC DISCONTINUED WITH NO REPLACEMENT ON 01/12/2024.|
UKBC|THE CLIMATIC CONDITIONS UNDER WHICH THE ITEM WILL PERFORM SATISFACTORILY.|
UKBD|THE LENGTH OF A STRAIGHT LINE WHICH PASSES THROUGH THE CENTER OF THE MAJOR PORTION OF THE MOUNTING HOLE.|
UKBF|THE LENGTH OF A STRAIGHT LINE WHICH PASSES THROUGH THE CENTER OF THE TUBE,AND TERMINATES AT THE INSIDE CIRCUMFERENCE.|
UKBG|THE MAXIMUM POTENTIAL GRADIENT THE INSULATING MATERIAL CAN WITHSTAND,PER UNIT THICKNESS,WITHOUT RUPTURE.|
UKBH|THE VOLTAGE MEASURED AT THE TERMINALS OF THE FUSE LINK WHEN THE MAXIMUM RATED CURRENT IS BEING CARRIED,EXPRESSED IN VOLTS.|
UKBJ|THE TIME BETWEEN THE COMMENCEMENT OF A CURRENT LARGE ENOUGH TO CAUSE A BREAK IN THE FUSE ELEMENT AND THE INSTANT WHEN THE ARC IS INITIATED AT A SPECIFIED PERCENTAGE OF ITS NORMAL CURRENT RATING,EXPRESSED IN SECONDS.|
UKBK|THE MAXIMUM CURRENT THAT A PROTECTIVE DEVICE WILL INTERRUPT OR SHORT CIRCUIT WITHOUT ABNORMAL SELF OR ENVIRONMENTAL DETERIORATION,EXPRESSED IN AMPERES. MRC DISCONTINUED WITH NO REPLACEMENT ON 01/12/2024.|
UKBL|THE PERMISSABLE DIFFERENCE OF THE AVERAGE DIAMETER OF THE INDIVIDUAL BALLS WITHIN ANY ONE UNIT CONTAINER.|
UKBM|THE MAXIMUM PERMISSABLE DEVIATION FROM A TRUE SPHERE DETERMINED BY TAKING A NUMBER OF MEASUREMENTS IN DIFFERENT PLANES AROUND THE BALL CIRCUMFERENCE.|
UKBN|THE SINGLE NOMINAL SIZE DESIGNATION THAT REPRESENTS MORE SPECIFIC CROSS-SECTIONAL DIMENSIONS OF THE ITEM.|
UKBP|AN INDICATION OF THE TEST REQUIREMENTS TO WHICH A SPRING CONFORMS.|
UKBQ|A SPECIFIED TEST LOAD WHICH THE ITEM MUST WITHSTAND WITHOUT DAMAGE.|
UKBR|THE HIGHEST POTENTIAL AND TYPE OF CURRENT THAT MAY BE CONTINUOUSLY APPLIED TO THE ITEM PER SECTION AT THE HIGHEST OPERATING TEMPERATURE PERMISSIBLE WITHOUT VOLTAGE DERATING,EXPRESSED IN VOLTS.|
UKBS|DIRECT CURRENT RESISTANCE BETWEEN TWO CONDUCTORS THAT ARE SEPARATED BY AN INSULATING MATERIAL,MEASURED AT 20 DEGREES CELSIUS.|
UKBT|AN INDICATION OF THE VALUE CONFIGURATION.|
UKBW|THE SPECIFIC POSITION OF THE POLARIZATION DEVICE.|
UKBX|THE DISTANCE FROM THE CENTER OF ONE CONTACT TO THE CENTER OF THE NEXT CONTACT.|
UKBY|THE SPECIFIC METHOD USED TO PREVENT MISMATING OF ITEMS HAVING THE SAME SHELL SIZE AND CONTACT ARRANGEMENT.|
UKBZ|THE DESIGNATOR THAT IDENTIFIES THE ANGULAR POSITION OF THE ORIENTATION METHOD.|
UKCA|THE DESIGNATION NUMBER IS EQUAL TO ONE-HUNDREDTH OF THE SPECIFIED PROOF LOAD STRESS IN NEWTON PER SQUARE MILLIMETERS. THIS PROOF LOAD STRESS CORRESPONDS TO THE MINIMUM TENSILE STRENGTH OF A BOLT OR SCREW WITH WHICH THE NUT SHOULD BE ASSEMBLED SO AS TO ENSURE THE LOADING CAPACITY OF THE BOLTED CONNECTION UP TO THE MINIMUM YIELD STRENGTH OF THE BOLT.|
UKCB|THE NOMINAL SIZE THAT INDICATES THE ACTUAL OUTSIDE DIAMETER OF THE ITEM ACCOMMODATED.|
UKCC|THE NUMBER(S), LETTER(S), AND/OR SYMBOLS IDENTIFYING A SPECIFIC ISSUE OF A MANUFACTURERS NUMBER WHICH WHEN ADDED TO THE SR-5 MANUFACTURERS NUMBER REPLY UNIQUELY IDENTIFIES THE DRAWING/FACSIMILE USED TO ESTABLISH THE CONCEPT OF THE ITEM BEING DESCRIBED.|
VANG|THE ANGLE OF VIEW.|
WAQS|A MEASUREMENT OF THE LONGEST DIMENSION OF THE SLOT, IN DISTINCTION FROM WIDTH.|
WDTH|A MEASUREMENT TAKEN AT RIGHT ANGLES TO THE LENGTH OF AN ITEM,IN DISTINCTION FROM THICKNESS.|
WGAA|SUM OF WINGS AREAS PROJECTED HORIZONTALLY.|
WGHT|A RELATIVE MEASURE OF THE MASS OF AN ITEM WITH RESPECT TO ITS DENSITY. PLEASE USE MRC ASHR IN PLACE OF THIS DISCONTINUED MRC.|
WKLG|NONE|
WLBL|THE WARNING LABEL CODE ASSIGNED BY THE DEPARTMENT OF TRANSPORTATION (DOT) TO EACH PACKAGE OR CONTAINMENT DEVICE OFFERED FOR TRANSPORTATION OF A HAZARDOUS MATERIAL WHICH MEETS ONE OR MORE HAZARD CLASS DEFINITIONS IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE TITLE 49 CODE OF FEDERAL REGULATIONS (CFR), PART 172, HAZARDOUS MATERIALS TABLE. THIS MRC HAS BEEN DISCONTINUED WITH NO REPLACEMENT - THIS INFORMATION IS NOT CHARACTERISTIC INFORMATION, THIS INFORMATION NEEDS TO BE INPUT IN SEG G OF THE TIR.|
WPNS|THE DSA REGISTRATION NUMBER ASSIGNED TO EACH SYSTEM TO IDENTIFY SUPPORTING ITEMS FOR SPECIAL MANAGEMENT AND TO OPTIMIZE AVAILABILITY AND DELIVERY OF ITEMS FROM STOCK.|
WPNT|THE NUMBER OF FIRING LINE(S) WHICH COULD BE CONNECTED TO THE ITEM.|
WPNU|THE NUMBER OF ELECTRIC BLASTING CAP(S) WHICH COULD BE INITIATED BY THE ITEM.|
WRSP|THE RATE AT WHICH DATA IS TRANSFERRED TO A STORAGE MEDIUM.|
ZZZK|THE DOCUMENT DESIGNATOR OF THE SPECIFICATION OR STANDARD WHICH ESTABLISHED THE ITEM OF SUPPLY.|
ZZZP|THE CONTROLLING ACTIVITY AND IDENTIFICATION OF A DOCUMENT USED IN LIEU OF A SPECIFICATION IN THE PROCUREMENT OF AN ITEM OF SUPPLY. THIS MRC HAS BEE DISCONTINUED AND IS NOT ELIGIBLE FOR REINSTATEMENT. PLEASE USE MRC PDNB IN PLACE OF THIS DISCONTINUED MRC.|
ZZZS|THE PROFESSIONAL GROUP,INDUSTRIAL ASSOCIATION,OR MANUFACTURER,S SPECIFICATION OR STANDARD WHICH ESTABLISHES THE ITEM OF SUPPLY BEING DESCRIBED. INCLUDES THE FEDERAL SUPPLY CODE FOR MANUFACTURER /FSCM/ OF THE ENTITY CONTROLLING THE DOCUMENT. (THIS INFORMATION WAS FORMERLY PROVIDED IN PART BY RESPONSES TO SR-1 FOR OTHER THAN GOVERNMENT CONTROLLED DOCUMENTS.)|
ZZZT|THE NUMBER, LETTER, OR SYMBOL INDICATING THE TYPE, STYLE, GRADE, CLASS, AND THE LIKE OF AN ITEM IN A NONIDENTIFYING SPECIFICATION OR STANDARD.|
ZZZV|THE JUSTIFICATION FOR THE ASSIGNMENT OF A FEDERAL SUPPLY CLASS /FSC/ TO AN ITEM BASED ON THE CLASSIFICATION OF THE NEXT HIGHER CLASSIFIABLE ASSEMBLY.|
ZZZW|THE TECHNICAL DIFFERENTIATING CHARACTERISTIC(S) OF AN ITEM OF SUPPLY THAT DEPART(S) FROM THE TEXT OF A SPECIFICATION OR A STANDARD IN THAT IT REPRESENTS A SELECTION OF CHARACTERISTICS STATED IN THE SPECIFICATION OR STANDARD AS BEING OPTIONAL OR A VARIATION FROM ONE OR MORE OF THE STATED CHARACTERISTICS OR AN ADDITIONAL CHARACTERISTIC NOT STATED IN THE SPECIFICATION OR STANDARD.|
ZZZX|THE VARIATION WHEN THE ITEM IS IN CONFORMITY WITH A TYPE DESIGNATOR COVERED BY A SPECIFICATION OR STANDARD, EXCEPT IN REGARD TO ONE OR MORE TECHNICAL DIFFERENTIATING CHARACTERISTICS.|
ZZZY|A FEATURE OF THE ITEM OF SUPPLY WHICH MUST BE SPECIFICALLY RECORDED WHEN THE REFERENCE NUMBER COVERS A RANGE OF ITEMS.|
